 Sequel to his conviction, former Abia State Governor,  Orji Kalu, was heard asking prison warders, “where are you taking us to?” Kalu had been sentenced to 12 years in prison in relation to a N7. 1bn fraud. Kalu, aftet the pronouncement also begged the prison warders not to handcuff him in public. “Where are you taking us to now? Please don’t handcuff me. I will follow you, ” the former governor said. Kalu’s associate,  Udeogu, was sentenced to 10 years in prison while the Justice Idris Mohammed ordered Slok Limited, the company which was used in perpetrating the fraud, to be wound up. The Federal High Court in Lagos had convicted the former governor of Abia State, Orji Uzor Kalu, who was charged with N7.1bn fraud. The court found him and his co-defendants guilty of the 39 counts filed against them by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission. Kalu was sentenced to 12 years imprisonment by Justice Mohammed Idris, who ordered the winding up of Kalu’s company, Slok Nigeria Limited. The company was charged as third defendant in the case. 